
get the channel details
Get-WinEvent -ListLog * | Select-Object LogName, RecordCount | Format-Table -AutoSize

C -->Program Data -->Datadog-->conf.d-->win32_event_log.d	  
instances:
  - path: Application
  - path: Security

logs:
    - type: windows_event
      channel_path: "Security"
      source: Server
      service: Security
      tags: [env:dev, src:os]

    - type: windows_event
      channel_path: "Application"
      source: myapp
      service: myapp-service
      tags: [env:dev, src:app]


Enable the log collection in datadog_agent.yaml
logs_enabled: true



net user testuser Password123! /add
net user testuser /delete

View security events
Get-WinEvent -LogName Security -MaxEvents 10
filter by event id

Create event manually
eventcreate /T INFORMATION /ID 1000 /L APPLICATION /D "Test event for monitoring"
Get-WinEvent -FilterHashtable @{LogName='Security'; Id=4624}
